             depos'd, That she was at the Prisoner's Lodgings, and several Things were brought by a young Gentlema n, (she being with her 3 or 4 Days) with Bock-holes in his Face, who kiss'd her, and talk'd to her.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17310428-24-person132">
                  Joseph 
                  Moore 
               <interp inst="t17310428-24-person132" type="surname" value="Moore"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17310428-24-person132" type="given" value="Joseph"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17310428-24-person132" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             depos'd, That a young Gentleman wanted a Porter, and he being at the 12 Bells in Fleet-Street, he employ'd him to carry a Parcel to a Baker's-Shop in Hatton-Garden (where the Prisoner lodg'd) that there was a Woman as the Door; but what the Things was he could not say.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17310428-24-person133">
                  Jane 
                  Hutton 
               <interp inst="t17310428-24-person133" type="surname" value="Hutton"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17310428-24-person133" type="given" value="Jane"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17310428-24-person133" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             depos'd, That she was there when the Porter brought the Things, and that there came a young Gentleman, who sat by the Fire, and a Gentlewoman, and that he desired her to pawn a Silver-Tankard , Salver, &amp;c. for 20 l.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="173104280006"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t17310428-24-person134">
